## Problem
Even with CLI tools, Mode A will not spawn agents unless the skill teaches **when/how** from ambient speech.

## Scope (I005 / B058)
Update `skill/hark/SKILL.md` + `skill/handsfree` + packaged copies under `packages/ultradyn-hark/skills/`.

## Playbook
On `ambient.prompt` intent such as:
- start / spin up / open / launch {claude|codex|grok|cursor|opencode|…}
- new / create herdr session {name}
- start X in {project/path} on {session}
- …and tell it / with prompt {…}

Agent steps:
1. Parse agent, cwd, session, kickoff from speech (ask once if cwd/session ambiguous).
2. Confirm when creating a **new** session or unclear cwd.
3. Run `hark session ensure` / `hark agent-start …` (prefer CLI over raw herdr).
4. TTS short ack with agent + cwd + session + target if known.
5. Do **not** treat spawn as pane delivery; stay outside Herdr as Mode A.
6. File dogfood bugs if herdr start fails mid-voice.

## Acceptance
- [ ] Skill section documents phrases, confirm policy, CLI cheatsheet rows
- [ ] handsfree + npm skill packages stay in sync (same content policy as prior releases)
- [ ] No requirement for library-side NLU (Mode A judgment owns speech parse)